{"label":"Proportion - 7","id":"proportion-7","list":[{"label":"True or False","type":"classifySentence","id":"true-false","commonData":{"title":"The following numbers are in proportion.","fontSize":"2rem"},"data":[{"types":[{"name":"True","text":"1, 2, 5, 10\n6, 8, 9, 12\n15, 25, 9, 15"},{"name":"False","text":"5, 15, 15, 25\n4, 16, 8, 36"}]},{"types":[{"name":"True","text":"4, 12, 21, 63\n48, 20, 432, 180\n  24, 312, 14, 182"},{"name":"False","text":"\n  5, 20, 72, 30"}]}]},{"type":"numberInput","id":"simplify","label":"Find x","data":{"title":"Find x","type":"word-problem","fontSize":"1.5rem","isSentence":false,"fracFontSize":"1.2rem","list":["x : 39 :: 6 : 8\nx = 6/8 × 39\n= ?0/?1 × 39\n= ?2/??1\n= ?3\n3, 4, 117, 29.25\n","2 : 5 :: x : 30\nx/30 = 2/5 \nx = 2/5 × ?0\n= 2 × ?1 = ?2\n30, 6, 12","4 : 7 :: 28 : x\nx/28 = ?0/?1\nx = ??0/??1 × 28\n= ??0 × ?2 = ?3\n7, 4, 7, 49"]}},{"type":"numberInput","id":"simplify-2","label":"Word Problems","data":{"title":"Word Problems","type":"word-problem","fracFontSize":"0.9rem","list":["Given the numbers: 6, 7, 18, 22. What number must be subtracted from each of the following numbers, so that they will be in proportion?\nLet us solve this by trial and error method. \nIf we subtract 1, we get \n?0 , ?1 , ?2 , ?3\nThey are not in proportion.\nLet us subtract 2, we get \n?4 , ?5 , ?6 , ?7\nThey are in proportion.\n5, 6, 17, 21, 4, 5, 16, 20 ","Rama runs a tailoring unit. In a week, the unit can produce 560 night suits. Rama gets an order for stitching 1200 night suits in 12 days. Will she be able to complete the work in time? If not, how many more days will she require to complete the order?\nNo. of suits produced in 1 day\n= ?0/?1 = ?2\nNo of days, it will take to stitch 1200 suits\n= 1200/?3 = ?4 days\nSo, she will not be able to complete the work in time, and requires ?5 more days.\n560, 7, 80, 80, 15, 3"]}}]}